    <cas:Sofa xmi:id="1" sofaNum="1" sofaID="_InitialView" mimeType="text" sofaString="[March 2021, NES &amp; GoS] The availability of cattle feed for milk production was generally acceptable in the monitored sites, with an average price of 1 220 SYP per kg recorded in March 2021 (23 percent increase m-o-m). The highest selling price was observed in both Hasakeh and Deir-ez-Zor at 1 800 SYP per kg, while the lowest price was recorded in Rural Damascus governorate at 1 100 SYP per kg, Aleppo governorate witnessed a significant increase in the average price of cattle feed for milk production with a 46 percent m-o-m increase, with the price reaching 1 400 SYP per Kg. Cattle feed for meat production (i.e. compound fodder pellets) was available across all the monitored governorates at an estimated price of 1 161 SYP per kg. Deir-ez-Zor recorded the highest price of cattle feed, which was sold for at least 1 800 SYP per kg."/>
    <cas:View sofa="1" members="8 19 24 29 34 39 52 65 78 91 104 117 130 143 156 169 182 195 208 221 234 247 260 273 286 299 312 325 338 351 364 377 390 403 416 429 442 455 468 481 494 507 520 533 546 559 572 585 598 611 624 637 650 663 676 689 702 715 728 741 754 767 780 793 806 819 832 845 858 871 884 897 910 923 936 949 962 975 988 1001 1014 1027 1040 1053 1066 1079 1092 1105 1118 1131 1144 1157 1170 1183 1196 1209 1222 1235 1248 1261 1274 1287 1300 1313 1326 1339 1352 1365 1378 1391 1404 1417 1430 1443 1456 1469 1482 1495 1508 1521 1534 1547 1560 1573 1586 1599 1612 1625 1638 1651 1664 1677 1690 1703 1716 1729 1742 1755 1768 1781 1794 1807 1820 1833 1846 1859 1872 1885 1898 1911 1924 1937 1950 1963 1976 1989 2002 2015 2028 2041 2054 2067 2080 2093 2106 2119 2132 2145 2158 2171 2176 2181 2210 2200 2205 2225 2215 2220 2314 2273 2230 2235 2240 2297 2292 2333 2357 2309 2345 2186 2193 2252 2245 2266 2259 2319 2326 2278 2285 2302 2338 2362 2350 2369 2376 2372 2379 2383 2396"/>
